My wife and I have tried so hard to like this place. We usually love Panera Bread. But, every single time that we’ve ordered from this particular Panera or have gone there to eat pre-COVID, they’ve messed up our order.  And it’s not like the mistakes were small; like I asked for no tomato, and then they put tomato on the sandwich (who cares, I can just pick it off). Instead, we’ll ask for a sandwich, no special requests, and we’ll get two pieces of bread (the wrong bread) with only meat on it (the wrong meat). Other times, we’ll order soup, and the soup will be packed in the bag, upside down, leaking all over the lobby of our building.  I don’t know what it is about this location, but they cannot get a single order right. Plus, they say that they check all of the orders before they are sent out, which obviously isn’t happening for the reasons above. Very disappointing.
